  <description><![CDATA[<p>It doesn't get much better than the Fairmont Chateau <a rel="noopener" data-udi="umb://document/7cf5e06f2ccd4cf8b8f46d06ca905a75" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7cf5e06f2ccd4cf8b8f46d06ca905a75}" target="_blank" title="Lake Louise">Lake Louise</a> with arguably the best setting and view of any hotel located in the Banff National Park.</p>
<h2>Lake views</h2>
<p>Each morning you can awake to views of the snowy lake, the dramatic Rocky Mountains and the stunning Victoria Glacier. The luxury hotel is great for everyone but particularly couples looking for that extra special getaway and we highly recommend upgrading to a lake view room. </p>
<h2>Location</h2>
<p>The hotel is located directly on the shores of Lake Louise. The convenient free shuttle service runs throughout the day providing access to the slopes and the Village. </p>
<h2>Dining </h2>
<p>The hotel has a great range of restaurants and bars to enjoy, but if you want to dine out a few nights and try some nice local restaurants and bars it couldn't be easier to get around. Back at the hotel there's plenty of things to keep you entertained.</p>
<h2>Winter activities</h2>
<p>Enjoy an evening campfire where you can toast marshmallows, take an afternoon off the slopes and try your hand at Bavarian curling, or relax in the spa. Our favourite activity is taking to the frozen lake on a set of ice skates and making the most incredible memories.</p>]]></description>
